{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01R9dFEgUXd4VcfqEQKeaDAi","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Story 12.4: Shared Test Utilities and Fixtures\n     2→\n     3→Status: review\n     4→\n     5→<!-- Note: Validation is optional. Run validate-create-story for quality check before dev-story. -->\n     6→\n     7→## Story\n     8→\n     9→As a developer,\n    10→I want reusable test helpers and fixtures,\n    11→So that tests don't duplicate mock setup across 50+ files.\n    12→\n    13→## Acceptance Criteria\n    14→\n    15→1. Given `src/lib/__tests__/fixtures/` exists, when inspected, then it contains: `cargo-toml-variants.ts`, `state-builders.ts`, `mock-factories.ts` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    16→2. Given `src/lib/__tests__/helpers.ts` exists, when test files import from it, then common patterns (mock Docker, mock fs, create temp state) are one-liners <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    17→3. Given `cargo-toml-variants.ts`, when inspected, then it exports named Cargo.toml string constants covering: minimal, actix-web, axum, async-openai, workspace, binary, library, and generic variants <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    18→4. Given `state-builders.ts`, when inspected, then it exports a `buildSprintState(overrides?: Partial<SprintState>): SprintState` factory that returns a valid SprintStateV2 object with sensible defaults <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    19→5. Given `mock-factories.ts`, when inspected, then it exports factory functions for commonly mocked modules: `createFsMock()`, `createChildProcessMock()`, `createDockerMock()`, `createStateMock()` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    20→6. Given `helpers.ts`, when inspected, then it exports `withTempDir(fn: (dir: string) => Promise<void>)` that creates a temp directory, runs the callback, and cleans up on completion or error <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    21→7. Given `helpers.ts`, when inspected, then it re-exports all fixtures and mock factories so consumers have a single import point <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    22→8. Given `npm test` runs after all changes, then all existing 3493+ tests pass with zero regressions <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    23→9. Given at least 3 existing test files are refactored to use the new shared utilities, when inspected, then their mock setup boilerplate is reduced (demonstrating the pattern works in practice) <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    24→10. Given no file in `src/lib/__tests__/fixtures/` or `src/lib/__tests__/helpers.ts`, when line count is checked, then no file exceeds 300 lines <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    25→\n    26→## Tasks / Subtasks\n    27→\n    28→- [x] Task 1 (AC: 1, 3): Create `src/lib/__tests__/fixtures/cargo-toml-variants.ts`\n    29→  - [x] Export named string constants for each Cargo.toml variant (minimal, actix-web, axum, async-openai, workspace, binary, library, generic)\n    30→  - [x] Extract inline Cargo.toml strings from `src/lib/__tests__/stacks/rust.test.ts` as the source of truth\n    31→- [x] Task 2 (AC: 1, 4): Create `src/lib/__tests__/fixtures/state-builders.ts`\n    32→  - [x] Import `SprintState` (aliased to `SprintStateV2`) from `src/types/state.ts`\n    33→  - [x] Export `buildSprintState(overrides?)` with sensible defaults (version 2, current date, empty stories array, etc.)\n    34→  - [x] Export `buildStoryEntry(overrides?)` for individual story objects\n    35→- [x] Task 3 (AC: 1, 5): Create `src/lib/__tests__/fixtures/mock-factories.ts`\n    36→  - [x] `createFsMock()` — returns vi.fn() stubs for readFileSync, writeFileSync, existsSync, mkdirSync, etc.\n    37→  - [x] `createChildProcessMock()` — returns vi.fn() stubs for execFileSync, spawn, etc.\n    38→  - [x] `createDockerMock()` — returns vi.fn() stubs for isStackRunning, startStack, stopStack, etc.\n    39→  - [x] `createStateMock()` — returns vi.fn() stubs for readLocalConfig, getProjectRoot, etc.\n    40→- [x] Task 4 (AC: 2, 6, 7): Create `src/lib/__tests__/helpers.ts`\n    41→  - [x] Export `withTempDir()` utility\n    42→  - [x] Re-export all from `./fixtures/cargo-toml-variants.ts`, `./fixtures/state-builders.ts`, `./fixtures/mock-factories.ts`\n    43→- [x] Task 5 (AC: 9): Refactor at least 3 existing test files to use shared utilities\n    44→  - [x] `src/lib/__tests__/stacks/rust.test.ts` — replace inline Cargo.toml strings with fixture imports\n    45→  - [x] `src/modules/sprint/__tests__/selector.test.ts` — replace inline makeState/makeBadState with shared builders\n    46→  - [x] `src/modules/sprint/__tests__/feedback.test.ts` — replace inline mockState with state-builders\n    47→- [x] Task 6 (AC: 8): Run full test suite — all tests pass, zero regressions\n    48→- [x] Task 7 (AC: 10): Verify all new files are under 300 lines\n    49→\n    50→## Dev Notes\n    51→\n    52→### Architecture Compliance\n    53→\n    54→- **Decision 4 (Domain Subdirectories):** The architecture specifies `src/lib/__tests__/fixtures/` for shared test data and `src/lib/__tests__/helpers.ts` for mock factories and state builders. Follow this exactly.\n    55→- **300-line limit (Decision 7, NFR5):** All new files must stay under 300 lines.\n    56→- **Import convention:** Test files importing shared utilities should use `import { ... } from '../../lib/__tests__/helpers.js'` (or relative equivalent). The `.js` extension is required for ESM resolution.\n    57→\n    58→### Duplication Analysis (Why This Story Matters)\n    59→\n    60→Current test codebase has significant duplication:\n    61→- **17 `vi.mock('node:fs', ...)` declarations** across test files\n    62→- **22 `vi.mock('node:child_process', ...)` declarations**\n    63→- **26 `vi.mock(...)` calls for Docker-related modules**\n    64→- **8 `vi.mock(...)` calls for state modules**\n    65→- Inline Cargo.toml string literals repeated across 14+ test assertions in `rust.test.ts`\n    66→- Each test file independently builds mock objects for the same modules\n    67→\n    68→### Testing Framework\n    69→\n    70→- **Vitest** (not Jest). Use `vi.fn()`, `vi.mock()`, `vi.mocked()`.\n    71→- Imports: `import { describe, it, expect, beforeEach, afterEach, vi } from 'vitest'`\n    72→\n    73→### Mock Factory Design Guidance\n    74→\n    75→Mock factories should return plain objects with `vi.fn()` stubs. They should NOT call `vi.mock()` themselves — that must happen at the module level in each test file (Vitest requirement: `vi.mock()` is hoisted). The factories provide the mock implementations that test files pass to `vi.mock()`.\n    76→\n    77→Example pattern:\n    78→```typescript\n    79→// In mock-factories.ts:\n    80→export function createFsMock() {\n    81→  return {\n    82→    readFileSync: vi.fn(),\n    83→    writeFileSync: vi.fn(),\n    84→    existsSync: vi.fn(() => true),\n    85→    mkdirSync: vi.fn(),\n    86→    mkdtempSync: vi.fn(),\n    87→    rmSync: vi.fn(),\n    88→  };\n    89→}\n    90→\n    91→// In a test file:\n    92→import { createFsMock } from '../../lib/__tests__/helpers.js';\n    93→const fsMock = createFsMock();\n    94→vi.mock('node:fs', () => fsMock);\n    95→```\n    96→\n    97→### State Builder Design Guidance\n    98→\n    99→The `buildSprintState()` factory must produce valid `SprintStateV2` objects. Reference `src/types/state.ts` for the interface (lines 97-127). Use `Partial<SprintState>` spread pattern for overrides.\n   100→\n   101→### Previous Story Intelligence (12-3)\n   102→\n   103→- Story 12-3 completed successfully. Pattern: extract from monolith into domain module, keep thin command layer.\n   104→- 3493 tests passing as of story 12-3 completion.\n   105→- Coverage: 97.09% overall, all 150 files above 80% per-file floor.\n   106→- Import boundaries test (`src/modules/__tests__/import-boundaries.test.ts`) enforces module isolation.\n   107→\n   108→### Refactoring Guidance\n   109→\n   110→When refactoring existing test files (Task 5), the approach is:\n   111→1. Import the shared utility\n   112→2. Replace the inline mock/fixture with the shared version\n   113→3. Run the specific test file to verify no regressions\n   114→4. Do NOT change test logic or assertions — only the mock setup\n   115→\n   116→### Project Structure Notes\n   117→\n   118→Target file tree after this story:\n   119→```\n   120→src/lib/__tests__/\n   121→  fixtures/\n   122→    cargo-toml-variants.ts   # Named Cargo.toml string constants\n   123→    state-builders.ts         # buildSprintState(), buildStoryEntry()\n   124→    mock-factories.ts         # createFsMock(), createChildProcessMock(), etc.\n   125→  helpers.ts                  # withTempDir(), re-exports all fixtures\n   126→  ... existing test files ...\n   127→```\n   128→\n   129→### References\n   130→\n   131→- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v3.md lines 273-275] — `src/lib/__tests__/` structure spec\n   132→- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-architecture-v3.md lines 237-251] — Story 12-4 epic definition\n   133→- [Source: src/types/state.ts lines 97-131] — SprintStateV2 interface definition\n   134→- [Source: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/12-3-move-status-logic-to-module.md] — Previous story learnings\n   135→\n   136→<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-START:story-verification -->\n   137→## Verification Requirements\n   138→\n   139→- [ ] Showboat proof document created (`docs/exec-plans/active/12-4-shared-test-utilities-fixtures.proof.md`)\n   140→- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified with real-world evidence\n   141→- [ ] Test coverage meets target (100%)\n   142→\n   143→## Documentation Requirements\n   144→\n   145→- [ ] Relevant AGENTS.md files updated (list modules touched)\n   146→- [ ] Exec-plan created in `docs/exec-plans/active/12-4-shared-test-utilities-fixtures.md`\n   147→\n   148→## Testing Requirements\n   149→\n   150→- [ ] Unit tests written for all new/changed code\n   151→- [ ] Integration tests for cross-module interactions\n   152→- [ ] Coverage target: 100%\n   153→<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-END:story-verification -->\n   154→\n   155→## Dev Agent Record\n   156→\n   157→### Agent Model Used\n   158→\n   159→Claude Opus 4.6 (1M context)\n   160→\n   161→### Debug Log References\n   162→\n   163→### Completion Notes List\n   164→\n   165→- Task 1: Created `cargo-toml-variants.ts` with 8 named Cargo.toml string constants (74 lines)\n   166→- Task 2: Created `state-builders.ts` with `buildSprintState`, `buildStoryEntry`, `buildEpicState`, `buildActionItem`, `buildSprintStateWithStory` (139 lines)\n   167→- Task 3: Created `mock-factories.ts` with `createFsMock`, `createChildProcessMock`, `createDockerMock`, `createStateMock` (96 lines)\n   168→- Task 4: Created `helpers.ts` with `withTempDir()` and re-exports of all fixtures (37 lines)\n   169→- Task 5: Refactored 3 test files: rust.test.ts (11 inline Cargo.toml strings replaced), feedback.test.ts (2 inline SprintState objects replaced), selector.test.ts (makeState/makeBadState replaced with shared builders). Note: docker.test.ts was originally targeted but replaced with selector.test.ts because `vi.mock()` hoisting prevents using factory imports inside `vi.mock()` callbacks — the mock factory pattern is most useful for mock *configuration* (return values), not `vi.mock()` declarations themselves.\n   170→- Task 6: Full test suite passes — 3539 tests across 134 files, zero regressions (up from 3493 due to 46 new tests)\n   171→- Task 7: All new files under 300 lines (max: 139 lines for state-builders.ts)\n   172→\n   173→### Change Log\n   174→\n   175→- 2026-03-24: Story 12-4 implemented — shared test utilities and fixtures\n   176→\n   177→### File List\n   178→\n   179→- src/lib/__tests__/fixtures/cargo-toml-variants.ts (new)\n   180→- src/lib/__tests__/fixtures/state-builders.ts (new)\n   181→- src/lib/__tests__/fixtures/mock-factories.ts (new)\n   182→- src/lib/__tests__/helpers.ts (new)\n   183→- src/lib/__tests__/fixtures/cargo-toml-variants.test.ts (new)\n   184→- src/lib/__tests__/fixtures/state-builders.test.ts (new)\n   185→- src/lib/__tests__/fixtures/mock-factories.test.ts (new)\n   186→- src/lib/__tests__/helpers.test.ts (new)\n   187→- src/lib/__tests__/stacks/rust.test.ts (modified)\n   188→- src/modules/sprint/__tests__/feedback.test.ts (modified)\n   189→- src/modules/sprint/__tests__/selector.test.ts (modified)\n   190→- src/lib/AGENTS.md (modified)\n   191→- docs/exec-plans/active/12-4-shared-test-utilities-fixtures.md (new)\n   192→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01E4d2UoNxdYuxQTG5Dezgge","session_id":"8c35c2f7-0e10-4994-a438-2b5cecce3396","uuid":"0ee6f15d-3c7c-4852-973c-e96709c02b97","timestamp":"2026-03-24T14:16:12.892Z"}
